<plot>'Our Own Piece of Sunshine' imparts the feelings and histories of five of Miami's historically black neighborhoods. From segregation to black on black racism to acceptance as part of the greater Miami melting pot, The film gives voice to the residents of the unique neighborhoods of Little Haiti, Overtown, Perrine, and the Jamaican and African communities. Miami as you've never seen it!</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?417686</url></doc>
